raw_data.name: Caffiend
raw_data.full_address: 5910 Waxhaw Hwy Suite D, Mineral Springs, NC 28108, United States
raw_data.description: Locally owned and operated coffee shop with local baked goods.
raw_data.typical_time_spent: People typically spend up to 45 min here

reviews_data.review_text: Great local coffee spot! Good quality and flavor. Friendly staff. Chill atmosphere. :)

I’ve passed by this place for so long and never realized it was here.  I’m so glad I discovered it this morning!   My latte was amazing and one of the few places I’ve seen that has pumpkin in the summer.  Shoutout to the girl working too, didn’t catch her name but she was so sweet.  Will be back for sure! 🩷
Atmosphere great and staff friendly. Coffee was great and hot. Enjoyed being in there.
The barista was so sweet! Amazing drinks!
We love this place.
We love this place! We come every weekend, relax while we drink our coffee’s they have games for our kids. It’s a calm environment. Exactly what we need on our weekends!
Quaint cute place

Very friendly!
Great coffee!

Kat was AMAZING! Very welcoming and helped me with it being my first time in. She was very patient with me and answered all of my questions, no matter how silly. Go check them out! Also, the CHEESECAKE BROWNIES are made in house and they are chefs kiss!
Quaint coffee shop and ice cream parlor. You should definitely stop in. They have seasonal drink specials.
Great local coffee shop just minutes from me. Small but just the right size place to just sit, converse and have a good local coffee.
Iced Caramel latte barely had any ice and too much milk. The ice was melted in two minutes leaving me a like warm flavorless drink.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Deven, sorry that you had a less than favorable experience! The ratio was clearly off a bit. That’s certainly not the experience we want you or anyone else to have. If you’ll give us another chance, your drink will be on us! Have a great day.

reviews_data.review_text: First time in and greeted right away - friendly service for sure. Atmosphere was quiet and inviting. Got a medium hot mocha and a cheese pastry. Coffee was hot and not too sweet however the pastry was not good at all. Hard/dried out - did not finish. For $9 I should have skipped the pastry and just had coffee. Would recommend just no food.

If you are driving around Mineral Springs, stop at Caffiend to get a coffee or a bakery sweet for the road. Caffiend has been open for roughly a year now serving coffee, cookies, slices of cake, cup cakes, and fruit. The prices are very reasonable compared to some big chain coffee houses. It has a down-home atmosphere with music playing inside and places to sit while you drink your coffee.

Cool little spot that makes a great Americano. They have a lot of sugar free flavor options for their latte's that actually taste great too! The guy working was very nice, but seemed overwhelmed when there's a line of people, so be prepared to wait. Prices are very fair.
Great place. Met the owner and his brother and they're really nice guys. I'll definitely be back
Support local. Delicious coffee and baked goods, warm comforting environment!
this coffee shop is great! i go there all the time because it’s amazing

This place is awesome! Love the ambiance and flavors of Caffiend! Highly suggest The Conductor. I really appreciate the spaces they have for different purposes and the games that are available as well. I could totally see their spaces being perfect for Bible studies, book clubs, or a work area.
Great place to hang out with friends or work related. Great little small business. The conductor was great!!!
This little coffee shop is so cute! They even have space available to have classes or birthday parties.
Very nice and quaint coffee shop.  My latte was delicious, and the owner very friendly.
Great new coffee shop. Will return for more good coffee and treats.

My cup was 4/5 of the way full, so I leave 4/5 stars

I recommend this establishment

We stopped in while visiting family. My husband said his latte was a little weak but I loved my “Conductor” latte. The atmosphere seemed like a great hang out spot or a place to work remotely. Comfortable but not crowded with lots of seating that ranged from typical wooden chairs to couches. There were a few board games on a table for anyone to play too.

It is refreshing to see a business that pays attention to the details and truly cares about making positive impressions. Both the coffee and treats are delicious. Everywhere you look, from the fresh flowers on the tables to the signage and self-serve station, it is clear these guys care about doing it right. Though it may seem pricey, please remember that they are in a low-volume geographic location, and therefore the prices are necessary to be able to stay  open and serve the Mineral Springs and Waxhaw community. I support them.
Cute coffee shop located in Mineral Springs. Great to see new and unique small businesses opening up here! I hope they have lots of success and support from the community!
Great atmosphere! Customer Service was good! Supporting local business is always important. Good spot to host a small meeting or host a group. Open until 1pm.

reviews_data.review_text: A much needed boost to the area coffee offerings. Fresh baked delicacies and a great variety of coffee. Stop in for a relaxing cup or grab one one the go. Owners are super friendly.
